# Regression: the `chr(code)` builtin turns an integer character code into a
# one-byte string. It is a first-class char<->code primitive (the inverse of
# `String.char_at`), used pervasively in libjn/strings. `chr(65)+chr(66)+chr(67)`
# builds "ABC"; `chr(48 + 7)` builds "7".

*main
    log(chr(65) + chr(66) + chr(67))
    log(chr(48 + 7))
